==English==
===Noun===
'''[[homologous]] [[series]]'''
#{{chemistry}} any series of [[aliphatic]] [[organic]] [[compound]]s whose members differ only in the [[addition]] of a CH<sub>2</sub> [[group]]; for example, the [[carboxylic acid]]s, CH<sub>3</sub>(CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>n</sub>COOH where n is any non-negative number. Each member of a homologous series also have differing physical properties but similar chemical properties, have the same name ending and conform to a genral formula. 

